1
00:00:13,467 --> 00:00:17,133
You might kill yourself
when you hear about this.

2
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:19,333
You can never fool me again.

3
00:00:19,467 --> 00:00:23,267
What if I tell you
that Red and Eden

4
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:24,867
are already getting married?

5
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:25,867
Gosh, Eden!

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,800
Why did you put your
wedding dress on?

7
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:29,200
That's the reason
we came here.

8
00:00:29,333 --> 00:00:30,700
To fit my gown.

9
00:00:30,833 --> 00:00:34,300
The elders believe that wearing
your wedding dress

10
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:37,633
before the wedding
brings bad luck.

11
00:00:37,767 --> 00:00:39,700
It's okay to try your
wedding dress nowadays.

12
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:45,800
To make sure it will fit
perfectly.

13
00:00:45,933 --> 00:00:49,100
Lucho, find out where Eden
and Red are getting married.

14
00:00:49,233 --> 00:00:50,867
Amanda, leave Eden be.

15
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,467
She has her own life now.

16
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:55,500
Once they get married, I can
never get my daughter back.

17
00:00:55,633 --> 00:00:57,033
You can't take her back anyway,

18
00:00:57,167 --> 00:00:59,033
even if she's not married
to Red yet.

19
00:00:59,167 --> 00:01:03,067
If I have to force her to come
back to me, I will!

20
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:06,967
Wear this ring as a sign
of my love and fidelity,

21
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:08,600
forever and ever.

22
00:01:09,967 --> 00:01:12,867
I won't say congratulations
and best wishes

23
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,533
because this wedding is off.

24
00:01:14,667 --> 00:01:16,433
Mom, are you really not going
to leave us alone?

25
00:01:16,567 --> 00:01:18,033
No. I'll take you with me.

26
00:01:18,167 --> 00:01:19,067
Don't touch her!

27
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,800
You're not going to decide
for her.

28
00:01:20,933 --> 00:01:22,300
She will make a choice.

29
00:01:22,433 --> 00:01:24,067
You're still just a boyfriend.

30
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:25,033
This is my daughter.

31
00:01:25,167 --> 00:01:26,200
Yen!

32
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:27,767
- Don't hurt my son!
- Red! Red!

33
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:32,767
Amanda is confident
because she has Lucho.

34
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:34,867
We can't just attack them.

35
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,667
I don't trust that Lucho.

36
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:38,100
Now you know his true colors.

37
00:01:38,233 --> 00:01:41,067
Take back the money you invested
in that business.

38
00:01:41,233 --> 00:01:44,133
You have no idea
what they did to me.

39
00:01:44,267 --> 00:01:46,600
They're worse than the devil.

40
00:01:52,667 --> 00:01:55,333
Are you hungry? Here, eat this.

41
00:01:55,467 --> 00:01:58,300
Now tell me.

42
00:01:58,433 --> 00:02:02,967
How does it feel to be rejected
by your own daughter?

43
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:04,333
You're a worthless mother!

44
00:02:04,467 --> 00:02:06,367
A worthless human!

45
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:14,500
Sorry, Mom.

46
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:16,600
I wasn't aware of what
had happened.

47
00:02:16,733 --> 00:02:19,100
I will give you everything
as long as you're here.

48
00:02:19,233 --> 00:02:23,833
You will let me choose the life
I want if you truly love me.

49
00:02:23,967 --> 00:02:27,000
I cannot accept Red for a son.

50
00:02:27,133 --> 00:02:29,633
Now, if you won't change
your mind,

51
00:02:29,767 --> 00:02:32,667
you will never leave this room.

52
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,667
Mom!

53
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,333
Mom, open the door!

54
00:02:37,467 --> 00:02:40,400
Why are you doing this?

55
00:02:40,533 --> 00:02:41,533
Mom, open the door!

56
00:02:41,667 --> 00:02:43,600
Why do you have to do this?

57
00:02:43,733 --> 00:02:45,800
Why do you have to lock me here?

58
00:02:45,933 --> 00:02:48,167
Aunt Dindi!

59
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,967
Hello, Yen? How are you?

60
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:39,667
Red...

61
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,633
Red, I'm okay.

62
00:03:40,767 --> 00:03:44,200
Except my door is locked.

63
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:46,967
Did they lock you up?

64
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:49,500
I don't think mom
has locked me up.

65
00:03:49,633 --> 00:03:50,933
I know her.

66
00:03:51,067 --> 00:03:52,633
I know that she's just scared.

67
00:03:52,767 --> 00:03:55,133
That's why she locked the door.

68
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:59,900
But if I gain her trust,

69
00:04:00,033 --> 00:04:02,233
I think she'll leave
the door unlocked.

70
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:03,267
No, no. They can't do this.

71
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,933
We can't be separated.

72
00:04:06,067 --> 00:04:10,467
Red, I want to clear up
some things too.

73
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:14,167
My mom told me something.

74
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:17,367
But I don't want to judge
your mom right away.

75
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,500
Don't believe your mom.

76
00:04:19,633 --> 00:04:22,900
She'll do everything to
undermine my mom's reputation.

77
00:04:23,033 --> 00:04:26,467
I'm confused, Red.

78
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:29,000
I feel bad for everything
my mom had gone through

79
00:04:29,167 --> 00:04:33,367
at the hands of Uncle Zandro
and Mama Rina.

80
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:35,600
My mom is a good person, Yen.

81
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:36,867
You know that.

82
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:41,600
If someone wants to harm us,
it's your mother.

83
00:04:41,733 --> 00:04:43,067
Give that to me.

84
00:04:46,567 --> 00:04:47,967
Hey, you.

85
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:50,500
How dare you. Stop calling
my daughter.

86
00:04:50,633 --> 00:04:54,167
You will never see
my daughter again!

87
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:58,333
Mom, please give it back to me.

88
00:04:58,467 --> 00:05:03,000
How often do I have to tell you
to forget Red?

89
00:05:03,167 --> 00:05:07,367
He will tell you nothing
but lies.

90
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,933
Are you going to control me
for life?

91
00:05:10,067 --> 00:05:11,000
Yes!

92
00:05:11,133 --> 00:05:14,800
Are you glad that I'm being
miserable?

93
00:05:14,933 --> 00:05:18,900
Yes, because you will be
more miserable with them.

94
00:05:19,033 --> 00:05:21,033
Mom, please!

95
00:05:21,167 --> 00:05:22,067
Don't do this to me.

96
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:26,200
I'm old enough. Let me decide
for myself!

97
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:28,833
Mom, open the door!

98
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:35,667
Amanda?

99
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:37,933
What happened?

100
00:05:38,067 --> 00:05:41,000
Why did you lock Eden up?

101
00:05:41,133 --> 00:05:44,167
I told her everything
that had happened to me.

102
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:47,300
She still chose Red
and his family.

103
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,867
Oh, dear!

104
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,800
I'm worried.

105
00:05:51,933 --> 00:05:56,400
She might become more upset with
you because of what you did.

106
00:05:56,533 --> 00:05:58,600
I need to be tough.

107
00:05:58,733 --> 00:06:02,000
If not, she might really choose
to be with Rina's family!

108
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:08,900
Don't you feel bad for her,
Amanda?

109
00:06:09,067 --> 00:06:12,533
No. I need to do this
for her sake.

110
00:06:18,833 --> 00:06:20,067
Auntie!

111
00:06:40,267 --> 00:06:41,533
Mom!

112
00:07:16,133 --> 00:07:17,833
Now, tell me.

113
00:07:18,867 --> 00:07:23,867
Should you love that family?

114
00:07:27,133 --> 00:07:29,300
Are you going to choose them
over me?

115
00:07:29,433 --> 00:07:33,600
Are you going to replace me with
the people who made me suffer?

116
00:07:34,567 --> 00:07:37,800
Are you still thinking
about your mom?

117
00:07:39,367 --> 00:07:40,300
Let me ask you.

118
00:07:40,433 --> 00:07:42,733
Do you think she still cares
for you?

119
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:47,133
All of these are your mom's
doing.

120
00:07:49,667 --> 00:07:52,100
No matter how often you
turn your back on me...

121
00:07:52,233 --> 00:07:53,500
leave me...

122
00:07:55,033 --> 00:07:56,633
I'll still be here.

123
00:07:57,667 --> 00:07:59,633
Even if you don't listen
to me...

124
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:04,367
I'll always be here
as your mother.

125
00:08:06,033 --> 00:08:09,700
Your mom doesn't care
for you, Eden.

126
00:08:11,167 --> 00:08:13,633
No matter how distant you
are from me...

127
00:08:17,633 --> 00:08:20,633
I can feel your suffering.

128
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:24,233
From the moment you were born...

129
00:08:26,233 --> 00:08:29,233
I've been carrying
a part of your heart.

130
00:08:30,533 --> 00:08:36,767
Now, I'm saying this
because I care for you.

131
00:08:37,233 --> 00:08:42,433
If you didn't go there, I would
have been married to Red by now.

132
00:08:42,567 --> 00:08:43,567
He would be your child too.

133
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:44,967
No, no.

134
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:46,467
I cannot accept that.

135
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,800
I cannot accept Red.

136
00:08:48,933 --> 00:08:51,333
I cannot accept Red for a son.

137
00:08:52,967 --> 00:08:54,300
He's a pest.

138
00:08:54,467 --> 00:08:58,067
He and his family bring nothing
but harm to our family.

139
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:00,800
Now, if you won't
change your mind...

140
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:04,200
you will never leave this room.

141
00:09:04,333 --> 00:09:05,400
Mom!

142
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:15,167
Yen, we brought you some food.

143
00:09:15,300 --> 00:09:18,567
Because you didn't want
to join us downstairs.

144
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:21,500
Thank you, Auntie.
I'm not hungry yet.

145
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,933
I heard you haven't eaten
anything yet.

146
00:09:24,067 --> 00:09:25,800
That's not right.

147
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:28,833
So, what's right?

148
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,900
Is it right for you to control
my life?

149
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:34,367
You won't win me over
with your hunger strike.

150
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:35,700
You have to eat.

151
00:09:36,733 --> 00:09:37,633
You're so stubborn.

152
00:09:37,767 --> 00:09:39,733
And change your clothes.

153
00:09:39,867 --> 00:09:40,767
There are clothes here.

154
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:42,433
Amanda, wait.

155
00:09:42,567 --> 00:09:43,767
I'll take care of her.

156
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:44,933
Go on.

157
00:09:45,067 --> 00:09:46,633
I'll talk some sense into her.

158
00:09:58,367 --> 00:10:00,867
Go on and eat.

159
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,233
Auntie, help me escape, please.

160
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:04,867
I feel like I'm losing it.

161
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:08,267
It feels like my mom
is making me a prisoner.

162
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:09,333
Come on.

163
00:10:09,467 --> 00:10:12,400
Running away isn't the solution
to your problem.

164
00:10:12,533 --> 00:10:15,200
Do you think we can escape
from here?

165
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:17,633
Bruno will surely catch us
if we try.

166
00:10:17,767 --> 00:10:20,033
His sense of smell is
sharper than a dog's.

167
00:10:20,167 --> 00:10:22,333
Auntie, please.

168
00:10:22,467 --> 00:10:23,900
It seems that she's
no longer my mom.

169
00:10:24,033 --> 00:10:25,600
She's changed a lot.

170
00:10:27,867 --> 00:10:31,533
Your mom loves you.

171
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:36,000
She was just hurt by what
happened to the two of you.

172
00:10:36,967 --> 00:10:40,133
If I were you, I would do
what she wanted for now.

173
00:10:40,267 --> 00:10:43,600
If not, she'll take you far away
from here.

174
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:45,033
- To where?
-She'll bring you somewhere far.

175
00:10:45,167 --> 00:10:46,500
I don't know where.
But, please!

176
00:10:46,633 --> 00:10:48,467
Do what she wants.

177
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,833
Where will mom bring me?

178
00:10:50,967 --> 00:10:53,300
I can't leave.

179
00:10:53,433 --> 00:10:54,767
Auntie...

180
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:56,000
Auntie, please.

181
00:10:56,133 --> 00:10:58,067
Please, help me escape.

182
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:01,300
I'll get crazy here.

183
00:11:01,433 --> 00:11:05,067
It's worse than death if my life
is going to be like this.

184
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,267
So, please.

185
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:08,367
Help me, Auntie, please.

186
00:11:08,533 --> 00:11:09,600
Please.

187
00:11:11,033 --> 00:11:12,400
Hold on.

188
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:14,533
Please, Auntie.

189
00:11:14,667 --> 00:11:16,500
I'll think of a way.

190
00:11:16,633 --> 00:11:18,167
But for now, do as your mom
says, please.

191
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:19,400
Sit down and eat first.

192
00:11:19,533 --> 00:11:20,633
You have to eat.

193
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:26,433
Hey.

194
00:11:27,467 --> 00:11:30,167
Lucho, can we talk?

195
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:31,400
Of course.

196
00:11:32,433 --> 00:11:33,600
Is it about Eden?

197
00:11:36,867 --> 00:11:39,100
Red won't leave her alone.

198
00:11:40,633 --> 00:11:48,967
I have a feeling that Red
will come and get her.

199
00:11:53,167 --> 00:11:54,333
Do you have a plan already?

200
00:11:54,467 --> 00:11:56,700
What plan do you have in mind?

201
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:01,233
I want to take her away
from here...

202
00:12:02,033 --> 00:12:04,933
to a place where Red
can't find her.

203
00:12:05,067 --> 00:12:06,833
Somewhere far.

204
00:12:07,633 --> 00:12:10,433
Do you know a place
where we can bring her?

205
00:12:10,567 --> 00:12:13,767
I have a rest house in Batangas.

206
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:16,133
It's in a secluded place.

207
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:18,800
Anyone will have a hard time
finding it.

208
00:12:21,067 --> 00:12:22,533
Can we go there?

209
00:12:22,667 --> 00:12:24,300
Just my daughter and me?

210
00:12:25,567 --> 00:12:26,667
Sure.

211
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:29,733
Tell me when you want to leave.

212
00:12:29,867 --> 00:12:32,033
I'll give her until tomorrow.

213
00:12:32,167 --> 00:12:37,700
If she doesn't change her mind,
I'll take her away from here.

214
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:38,967
I won't let her know...

215
00:12:39,100 --> 00:12:40,567
I won't let Dindi know.

216
00:13:03,133 --> 00:13:07,233
I hope Eden likes
what I bought her.

217
00:13:07,367 --> 00:13:09,967
So that she'll be
less upset with me.

218
00:13:12,033 --> 00:13:15,267
Everyone gets happy
with expensive things.

219
00:13:18,667 --> 00:13:21,000
You don't know my daughter,
Lucho.

220
00:13:21,167 --> 00:13:24,533
She's not into material things.

221
00:13:24,667 --> 00:13:26,033
She grew up poor.

222
00:13:27,133 --> 00:13:28,200
I'll check on your mom first.

223
00:13:28,333 --> 00:13:29,767
I'll leave you my phone.

224
00:13:29,900 --> 00:13:31,767
- I'll check on her first.
- Thank you, Auntie.

225
00:13:56,167 --> 00:13:57,033
Hello?

226
00:13:57,167 --> 00:13:59,300
Hello, Red?

227
00:13:59,433 --> 00:14:01,267
Yenyen!

228
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:03,867
Red, I just borrowed
Aunt Dindi's phone.

229
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,167
My mom took my phone.

230
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:09,800
That's why I couldn't
contact you.

231
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:11,400
Red, I'm in a rush.

232
00:14:11,533 --> 00:14:12,767
My mom will bring me somewhere.

233
00:14:12,900 --> 00:14:15,600
I don't know where, but we might
not see each other anymore.

234
00:14:15,733 --> 00:14:17,567
I won't let that happen.

235
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:18,633
I'll come and get you.

236
00:14:18,767 --> 00:14:21,400
No, no, don't.
Don't do that, Red.

237
00:14:21,533 --> 00:14:24,067
You can't get in here.
Bruno might hurt you.

238
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:26,367
I don't care about them.
Wait for me there.

239
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:39,133
The more she's eager to have
things she doesn't have.

240
00:14:39,267 --> 00:14:44,233
Who would not be happy
with lots of money?

241
00:14:44,367 --> 00:14:45,533
Me.

242
00:14:48,633 --> 00:14:51,133
Are you not happy with me?

243
00:14:51,267 --> 00:14:57,867
Lucho, I told you from the start
that I'd be honest with you.

244
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:02,300
And I'm honest with my feelings
for you.

245
00:15:02,467 --> 00:15:07,733
But I don't know why I feel like
something is missing.

246
00:15:07,867 --> 00:15:14,233
Eden is with me now,
but I'm still unhappy.

247
00:15:14,367 --> 00:15:17,067
I don't know.

248
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:23,700
I know you only wanted to
be with your daughter.

249
00:15:23,833 --> 00:15:27,933
And it will happen,

250
00:15:28,067 --> 00:15:29,900
especially now that you already
have her.

251
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:34,533
Your daughter will warm up
to you.

252
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:36,533
I hope so.

253
00:15:36,667 --> 00:15:39,000
But if that doesn't happen,

254
00:15:39,133 --> 00:15:44,400
I have no choice but to take her
away from Red.

255
00:15:44,533 --> 00:15:49,033
You can also take Red
away from her.

256
00:15:57,033 --> 00:15:57,800
Oh, dear!

257
00:15:57,933 --> 00:15:59,000
This is making me nervous.

258
00:15:59,133 --> 00:16:00,867
What's taking Red so long?

259
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,567
Your mom went out
with your Uncle Lucho.

260
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:04,233
And Bruno is driving for them.

261
00:16:04,367 --> 00:16:05,233
Red should be here
before they do.

262
00:16:05,367 --> 00:16:07,567
If not, Bruno will beat him up!

263
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:10,267
I hope my mom won't catch Red.

264
00:16:16,667 --> 00:16:19,300
Hello, Red?

265
00:16:19,433 --> 00:16:20,400
Hello, Yen?

266
00:16:20,533 --> 00:16:22,900
I'm outside your house.

267
00:16:23,033 --> 00:16:26,300
Wait for me. I'll come
and get you.

268
00:16:26,433 --> 00:16:29,300
Oh my god, Red. My mom
and Uncle Lucho might see you.

269
00:16:29,433 --> 00:16:33,467
There's no one here
since I came.

270
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,367
Hold on.

271
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:38,267
I'll find another way in,
so they won't notice me.

272
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:41,333
Okay. I'll go downstairs.

273
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:42,933
Auntie, I need to go.

274
00:16:43,067 --> 00:16:44,267
What? Hold on.

275
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:45,333
Okay, come on.

276
00:16:45,467 --> 00:16:47,967
Your mom might arrive
any moment.

277
00:16:58,133 --> 00:16:59,500
Who is it?

278
00:16:59,633 --> 00:17:01,133
Why aren't you answering
the call?

279
00:17:29,767 --> 00:17:31,900
I don't know who it is.

280
00:17:32,033 --> 00:17:34,100
It's not in my directory.

281
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:43,533
Go on and escape! Hurry up!

282
00:17:43,667 --> 00:17:45,200
Oh my god, Auntie.

283
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:47,900
Auntie, thank you so much.

284
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:51,167
I know you covered for me
so many times.

285
00:17:51,300 --> 00:17:52,933
- I'm sorry, Auntie.
- I love you so much.

286
00:17:53,067 --> 00:17:57,300
- I will never forget you.
- I love you so much.

287
00:17:57,433 --> 00:17:58,533
Eden, listen.

288
00:17:58,667 --> 00:18:02,133
I know you and Red
love each other.

289
00:18:02,267 --> 00:18:04,600
But you should always be smart.

290
00:18:04,733 --> 00:18:08,033
Always be cautious.

291
00:18:08,167 --> 00:18:11,733
I know that Red can take care
of you.

292
00:18:11,867 --> 00:18:14,400
But I don't trust the people
around him,

293
00:18:14,533 --> 00:18:18,600
especially Rina, that witch.

294
00:18:18,733 --> 00:18:19,733
Please?

295
00:18:19,867 --> 00:18:21,400
I'll pray for you. Go on.

296
00:18:21,567 --> 00:18:23,500
Don't worry, Auntie.
I'll be careful.

297
00:18:23,633 --> 00:18:24,567
Take care of yourself,
too, okay?

298
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:27,067
Go on, leave. Run away!

299
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,733
I will miss you, Auntie.

300
00:18:28,867 --> 00:18:30,433
Oh my god. Go on, leave!

301
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:54,833
Zandro?

302
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,467
Why did you call only now?

303
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:58,867
You know I'm wanted
by the police.

304
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,567
I'm glad you're out of jail now.

305
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:02,933
I posted bail.

306
00:19:03,067 --> 00:19:06,233
But Amanda won't leave me alone.

307
00:19:08,333 --> 00:19:11,400
We can't get back at her
on a whim.

308
00:19:11,533 --> 00:19:14,933
Because she has Lucho,
who's powerful.

309
00:19:15,067 --> 00:19:16,667
What do you want me to do?

310
00:19:24,967 --> 00:19:29,367
I want her out of our lives.

311
00:19:29,533 --> 00:19:34,300
And I know what we can do.

312
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:46,100
- Yen!
- Red!

313
00:19:46,233 --> 00:19:47,700
Red, are you okay?
Does anything hurt?

314
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:48,633
I'm okay.
How about you? Are you okay?

315
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:50,600
I'm glad you're out.

316
00:19:50,733 --> 00:19:52,300
I owe it to Aunt Dindi.

317
00:19:52,433 --> 00:19:55,133
If not for her, I would be
taken away by my mom.

318
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:57,200
Yen, we have to go.

319
00:19:57,333 --> 00:19:58,800
My car is parked across
from this house.

320
00:20:11,267 --> 00:20:13,000
Red! My mom's here!

321
00:20:13,133 --> 00:20:14,200
Come on!

322
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:01,167
I'm already here, Rina.

323
00:21:26,767 --> 00:21:27,767
Let's eat first.

324
00:21:27,900 --> 00:21:29,800
I told you we should have eaten
out earlier.

325
00:21:29,933 --> 00:21:31,300
- Join me.
- Okay.

326
00:21:31,433 --> 00:21:32,733
Wait.

327
00:21:34,067 --> 00:21:35,167
Hello, Dindi?

328
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:38,367
Amanda, my stomach hurts
so much.

329
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:39,867
Your stomach hurts?

330
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,367
Okay, I'll be there.

331
00:21:42,533 --> 00:21:44,200
- I'll check on Dindi.
- Okay.

332
00:21:57,167 --> 00:21:58,700
Hey.

333
00:21:58,833 --> 00:21:59,733
Yes, Jimmy?

334
00:22:01,033 --> 00:22:03,867
I'll check the file
in my office first.

335
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:05,733
Give me a second, okay?

336
00:22:16,167 --> 00:22:17,233
Eden?

337
00:22:17,833 --> 00:22:18,967
Eden?

338
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:20,333
Eden!

339
00:22:20,467 --> 00:22:21,633
Eden!

340
00:22:21,767 --> 00:22:22,700
Hello?

341
00:22:22,833 --> 00:22:24,767
Go on and leave! Hurry up!

342
00:22:24,900 --> 00:22:26,300
I already did what you told me.

343
00:22:26,433 --> 00:22:28,400
I ruined Lucho's car brakes.

344
00:22:28,533 --> 00:22:30,167
Very good!

345
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:32,567
I hope you did it well.

346
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:34,233
This will be the end of him.

347
00:22:34,367 --> 00:22:35,367
Eden's not here!

348
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:36,867
What happened?

349
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,300
Let's follow them!

350
00:22:38,433 --> 00:22:40,000
They can't run away from us!

351
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:42,767
Follow their car! There!

352
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:44,600
Red, someone's following us.

353
00:22:46,367 --> 00:22:47,200
Where's my son?

354
00:22:47,333 --> 00:22:48,267
I've been here for a while now.

355
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:50,500
I haven't seen Red.

356
00:22:50,667 --> 00:22:55,700
What if they took Red
using that car?

357
00:22:56,533 --> 00:22:57,467
Red, what's the matter?

358
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,267
The brake isn't working.

359
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:00,633
What?

360
00:23:01,933 --> 00:23:03,667
Red, what do we do?
